name: microservice-media-system
description: A simplified media platform. The system is comprised of three microservices, each of which produces and/or consumes events using Kafka. Each microservice is interacted with via an HTTP API using a command-line interface; these interactions alongside the Kafka messaging comprises the scope of the system.

name: Sophie
description: Sophie is a permission management system based on a distributed microservices architecture.

name: Microservices-based-Order-Management-System-with-Kafka
description: Seller and enduser app for generating bill on purchase and sending notification using Kafka

name: Scalable-Microservices
description: This application is a robust, scalable web platform built using a microservices architecture. It demonstrates advanced techniques in distributed systems design, focusing on high performance, reliability, and maintainability.

name: fast-food-crm-application
description: Fast Food Ordering System (Spring Microservices & Spring AI Chat Support)

name: JinfoTeur
description: Information System Manager that uses cloud hosting technologies, Go Microservices and Vue 3 related frontend technologies.

name: ailab-services
description: This repository contains the backend microservices for the AILab microblogging platform, designed to handle the core functionalities of the system.

name: ms-nest.js
description: This repository contains a microservice built with NestJS, a progressive Node.js framework for building efficient and scalable server-side applications. The microservice is designed to perform a specific function within a distributed system, communicating with other services via messaging protocols such as HTTP, TCP, or gRPC.

name: InventoryOne
description: A microservices-based inventory management system featuring a Go backend and a React/TypeScript frontend. Utilizes Kafka for messaging and MongoDB for storage. The application is containerized using Docker, and includes services for inventory, notifications, orders, shipments, auth, and user.

name: FrontEnd-MealMate
description: A modular Angular-based frontend for an advanced food ordering system. Integrates with a Spring Boot backend using a microservices architecture, backed by MySQL and MongoDB databases. Backend services will be linked here after their repositories are created and updated.

name: antibruteforce
description: AntibruteForce: A high-performance Go microservice for preventing password brute-force attacks. Utilizes GCRA algorithm, Redis for bucket storage, and PostgreSQL for IP white/blacklisting. Features gRPC API and CLI for easy management. Designed for server-to-server integration in authentication systems.
